516  /// copy constructor implementation
517  String::String(const String& obj) {
518  /// object member can be just copied by value
519  this->value = obj.value;
520 
521  /// if there is a token, make copy
522  if (obj.token) {
523  this-> token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
524  }
525 
526  /// set parents
527  set_parent_in_children();
528  }

590 
591  /// copy constructor implementation
592  Integer::Integer(const Integer& obj) {
593  /// object member can be just copied by value
594  this->value = obj.value;
595  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
596  if (obj.macro) {
597  this->macro.reset(obj.macro->clone());
598  }
599 
600  /// if there is a token, make copy
601  if (obj.token) {
602  this-> token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
603  }
604 
605  /// set parents
606  set_parent_in_children();
607  }
608 
609 
610  /// set this parent in the children
611  void Integer::set_parent_in_children() {
612 
613  /// optional member could be nullptr
614  if (macro) {
615  macro->set_parent(this);
616  }
617 
618  }

2791 /**
2792  * \brief Erase member to definitions
2793  */
2794 AssignedDefinitionVector::const_iterator AssignedBlock::erase_assigned_definition(AssignedDefinitionVector::const_iterator first) {
2795  auto first_it = const_iter_cast(definitions, first);
2796  return definitions.erase(first_it);
2797 }
2798 /**
2799  * \brief Erase members to definitions
2800  */
2801 AssignedDefinitionVector::const_iterator AssignedBlock::erase_assigned_definition(AssignedDefinitionVector::const_iterator first, AssignedDefinitionVector::const_iterator last) {
2802  auto first_it = const_iter_cast(definitions, first);
2803  auto last_it = const_iter_cast(definitions, last);
2804  return definitions.erase(first_it, last_it);
2805 }
2806 /**
2807  * \brief Erase non-consecutive members to definitions
2808  *
2809  * loosely following the cpp reference of remove_if
2810  */
2811 size_t AssignedBlock::erase_assigned_definition(std::unordered_set<AssignedDefinition*>& to_be_erased) {
2812  auto first = definitions.begin();
2813  auto last = definitions.end();
2814  auto result = first;
2815 
2816  while (first != last) {
2817  // automatically erase dangling pointers from the uset while
2818  // looking for them to erase them in the vector
2819  if (to_be_erased.erase(first->get()) == 0) {
2820  reset_assigned_definition(result, *first);
2821  ++result;
2822  }
2823  ++first;
2824  }
2825 
2826  size_t out = last - result;
2827  erase_assigned_definition(result, last);
2828 
2829  return out;
2830 }
2831 
2832 /**
2833  * \brief Insert member to definitions
2834  */
2835 AssignedDefinitionVector::const_iterator AssignedBlock::insert_assigned_definition(AssignedDefinitionVector::const_iterator position, const std::shared_ptr<AssignedDefinition>& n) {
2836  n->set_parent(this);
2837  auto pos_it = const_iter_cast(definitions, position);
2838  return definitions.insert(pos_it, n);
2839 }
2840 
2841 /**
2842  * \brief Reset member to definitions
2843  */
2844 void AssignedBlock::reset_assigned_definition(AssignedDefinitionVector::const_iterator position, AssignedDefinition* n) {
2845  //set parents
2846  n->set_parent(this);
2847 
2848  definitions[position - definitions.begin()].reset(n);
2849 }
2850 
2851 /**
2852  * \brief Reset member to definitions
2853  */
2854 void AssignedBlock::reset_assigned_definition(AssignedDefinitionVector::const_iterator position, std::shared_ptr<AssignedDefinition> n) {
2855  //set parents
2856  n->set_parent(this);
2857 
2858  definitions[position - definitions.begin()] = n;
2859 }

3388 /**
3389  * \brief Erase member to statements
3390  */
3391 StatementVector::const_iterator StatementBlock::erase_statement(StatementVector::const_iterator first) {
3392  auto first_it = const_iter_cast(statements, first);
3393  return statements.erase(first_it);
3394 }
3395 /**
3396  * \brief Erase members to statements
3397  */
3398 StatementVector::const_iterator StatementBlock::erase_statement(StatementVector::const_iterator first, StatementVector::const_iterator last) {
3399  auto first_it = const_iter_cast(statements, first);
3400  auto last_it = const_iter_cast(statements, last);
3401  return statements.erase(first_it, last_it);
3402 }
3403 /**
3404  * \brief Erase non-consecutive members to statements
3405  *
3406  * loosely following the cpp reference of remove_if
3407  */
3408 size_t StatementBlock::erase_statement(std::unordered_set<Statement*>& to_be_erased) {
3409  auto first = statements.begin();
3410  auto last = statements.end();
3411  auto result = first;
3412 
3413  while (first != last) {
3414  // automatically erase dangling pointers from the uset while
3415  // looking for them to erase them in the vector
3416  if (to_be_erased.erase(first->get()) == 0) {
3417  reset_statement(result, *first);
3418  ++result;
3419  }
3420  ++first;
3421  }
3422 
3423  size_t out = last - result;
3424  erase_statement(result, last);
3425 
3426  return out;
3427 }
3428 
3429 /**
3430  * \brief Insert member to statements
3431  */
3432 StatementVector::const_iterator StatementBlock::insert_statement(StatementVector::const_iterator position, const std::shared_ptr<Statement>& n) {
3433  n->set_parent(this);
3434  auto pos_it = const_iter_cast(statements, position);
3435  return statements.insert(pos_it, n);
3436 }
3437 
3438 /**
3439  * \brief Reset member to statements
3440  */
3441 void StatementBlock::reset_statement(StatementVector::const_iterator position, Statement* n) {
3442  //set parents
3443  n->set_parent(this);
3444 
3445  statements[position - statements.begin()].reset(n);
3446 }
3447 
3448 /**
3449  * \brief Reset member to statements
3450  */
3451 void StatementBlock::reset_statement(StatementVector::const_iterator position, std::shared_ptr<Statement> n) {
3452  //set parents
3453  n->set_parent(this);
3454 
3455  statements[position - statements.begin()] = n;
3456 }

5600  ForNetcon::ForNetcon(const ForNetcon& obj) {
5601  /// copy each element of vector
5602  for (auto& item : obj.parameters) {
5603  this->parameters.emplace_back(item->clone());
5604  }
5605  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
5606  if (obj.statement_block) {
5607  this->statement_block.reset(obj.statement_block->clone());
5608  }
5609 
5610  /// if there is a token, make copy
5611  if (obj.token) {
5612  this-> token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
5613  }
5614 
5615  /// set parents
5616  set_parent_in_children();
5617  }

5621  void ForNetcon::set_parent_in_children() {
5622

5624  for (auto& item : parameters) {
5625  item->set_parent(this);
5626 
5627  }
5628  /// optional member could be nullptr
5629  if (statement_block) {
5630  statement_block->set_parent(this);
5631  }
5632 
5633  }

5732 
5733  /// copy constructor implementation
5734  KineticBlock::KineticBlock(const KineticBlock& obj) {
5735  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
5736  if (obj.name) {
5737  this->name.reset(obj.name->clone());
5738  }
5739  /// copy each element of vector
5740  for (auto& item : obj.solvefor) {
5741  this->solvefor.emplace_back(item->clone());
5742  }
5743  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
5744  if (obj.statement_block) {
5745  this->statement_block.reset(obj.statement_block->clone());
5746  }
5747 
5748  /// if there is a token, make copy
5749  if (obj.token) {
5750  this-> token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
5751  }
5752 
5753  /// set parents
5754  set_parent_in_children();
5755  }
5756 
5757 
5758  /// set this parent in the children
5759  void KineticBlock::set_parent_in_children() {
5760 
5761  /// optional member could be nullptr
5762  if (name) {
5763  name->set_parent(this);
5764  }
5765  /// set parent for each element of the vector
5766  for (auto& item : solvefor) {
5767  item->set_parent(this);
5768 
5769  }
5770  /// optional member could be nullptr
5771  if (statement_block) {
5772  statement_block->set_parent(this);
5773  }
5774 
5775  }

7299  /// copy constructor implementation
7300  BinaryExpression::BinaryExpression(const BinaryExpression& obj) {
7301  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
7302  if (obj.lhs) {
7303  this->lhs.reset(obj.lhs->clone());
7304  }
7305  /// object member can be just copied by value
7306  this->op = obj.op;
7307  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
7308  if (obj.rhs) {
7309  this->rhs.reset(obj.rhs->clone());
7310  }
7311 
7312  /// if there is a token, make copy
7313  if (obj.token) {
7314  this-> token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
7315  }
7316 
7317  /// set parents
7318  set_parent_in_children();
7319  }
7320

7324 
7325  /// optional member could be nullptr
7326  if (lhs) {
7327  lhs->set_parent(this);
7328  }
7329  op.set_parent(this);
7330  /// optional member could be nullptr
7331  if (rhs) {
7332  rhs->set_parent(this);
7333  }
7334 
7335  }

7861  FunctionCall::FunctionCall(const FunctionCall& obj) {
7862  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
7863  if (obj.name) {
7864  this->name.reset(obj.name->clone());
7865  }
7866  /// copy each element of vector
7867  for (auto& item : obj.arguments) {
7868  this->arguments.emplace_back(item->clone());
7869  }
7870 
7871  /// if there is a token, make copy
7872  if (obj.token) {
7873  this-> token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
7874  }
7875 
7876  /// set parents
7877  set_parent_in_children();
7878  }

7886  name->set_parent(this);
7887  }
7888  /// set parent for each element of the vector
7889  for (auto& item : arguments) {
7890  item->set_parent(this);
7891 
7892  }
7893 
7894  }

8908 LocalVarVector::const_iterator LocalListStatement::erase_local_var(LocalVarVector::const_iterator first) {
8909  auto first_it = const_iter_cast(variables, first);
8910  return variables.erase(first_it);
8911 }
8912 /**
8913  * \brief Erase members to variables
8914  */
8915 LocalVarVector::const_iterator LocalListStatement::erase_local_var(LocalVarVector::const_iterator first, LocalVarVector::const_iterator last) {
8916  auto first_it = const_iter_cast(variables, first);
8917  auto last_it = const_iter_cast(variables, last);
8918  return variables.erase(first_it, last_it);
8919 }
8920 /**
8921  * \brief Erase non-consecutive members to variables
8922  *
8923  * loosely following the cpp reference of remove_if
8924  */
8925 size_t LocalListStatement::erase_local_var(std::unordered_set<LocalVar*>& to_be_erased) {
8926  auto first = variables.begin();
8927  auto last = variables.end();
8928  auto result = first;
8929 
8930  while (first != last) {
8931  // automatically erase dangling pointers from the uset while
8932  // looking for them to erase them in the vector
8933  if (to_be_erased.erase(first->get()) == 0) {
8934  reset_local_var(result, *first);
8935  ++result;
8936  }
8937  ++first;
8938  }
8939 
8940  size_t out = last - result;
8941  erase_local_var(result, last);
8942 
8943  return out;
8944 }
8945 
8946 /**
8947  * \brief Insert member to variables
8948  */
8949 LocalVarVector::const_iterator LocalListStatement::insert_local_var(LocalVarVector::const_iterator position, const std::shared_ptr<LocalVar>& n) {
8950  n->set_parent(this);
8951  auto pos_it = const_iter_cast(variables, position);
8952  return variables.insert(pos_it, n);
8953 }
8954 
8955 /**
8956  * \brief Reset member to variables
8957  */
8958 void LocalListStatement::reset_local_var(LocalVarVector::const_iterator position, LocalVar* n) {
8959  //set parents
8960  n->set_parent(this);
8961 
8962  variables[position - variables.begin()].reset(n);
8963 }
8964 
8965 /**
8966  * \brief Reset member to variables
8967  */
8968 void LocalListStatement::reset_local_var(LocalVarVector::const_iterator position, std::shared_ptr<LocalVar> n) {
8969  //set parents
8970  n->set_parent(this);
8971 
8972  variables[position - variables.begin()] = n;
8973 }

11305  /// copy constructor implementation
11306  IfStatement::IfStatement(const IfStatement& obj) {
11307  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
11308  if (obj.condition) {
11309  this->condition.reset(obj.condition->clone());
11310  }
11311  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
11312  if (obj.statement_block) {
11313  this->statement_block.reset(obj.statement_block->clone());
11314  }
11315  /// copy each element of vector
11316  for (auto& item : obj.elseifs) {
11317  this->elseifs.emplace_back(item->clone());
11318  }
11319  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
11320  if (obj.elses) {
11321  this->elses.reset(obj.elses->clone());
11322  }
11323 
11324  /// if there is a token, make copy
11325  if (obj.token) {
11326  this-> token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
11327  }
11328 
11329  /// set parents
11330  set_parent_in_children();
11331  }
11332

11334  /// set this parent in the children
11335  void IfStatement::set_parent_in_children() {
11336 
11337  /// optional member could be nullptr
11338  if (condition) {
11339  condition->set_parent(this);
11340  }
11341  /// optional member could be nullptr
11342  if (statement_block) {
11343  statement_block->set_parent(this);
11344  }
11345  /// set parent for each element of the vector
11346  for (auto& item : elseifs) {
11347  item->set_parent(this);
11348 
11349  }
11350  /// optional member could be nullptr
11351  if (elses) {
11352  elses->set_parent(this);
11353  }
11354 
11355  }

12190 /**
12191  * \brief Erase member to statements
12192  */
12193 WatchVector::const_iterator WatchStatement::erase_watch(WatchVector::const_iterator first) {
12194  auto first_it = const_iter_cast(statements, first);
12195  return statements.erase(first_it);
12196 }
12197 /**
12198  * \brief Erase members to statements
12199  */
12200 WatchVector::const_iterator WatchStatement::erase_watch(WatchVector::const_iterator first, WatchVector::const_iterator last) {
12201  auto first_it = const_iter_cast(statements, first);
12202  auto last_it = const_iter_cast(statements, last);
12203  return statements.erase(first_it, last_it);
12204 }
12205 /**
12206  * \brief Erase non-consecutive members to statements
12207  *
12208  * loosely following the cpp reference of remove_if
12209  */
12210 size_t WatchStatement::erase_watch(std::unordered_set<Watch*>& to_be_erased) {
12211  auto first = statements.begin();
12212  auto last = statements.end();
12213  auto result = first;
12214 
12215  while (first != last) {
12216  // automatically erase dangling pointers from the uset while
12217  // looking for them to erase them in the vector
12218  if (to_be_erased.erase(first->get()) == 0) {
12219  reset_watch(result, *first);
12220  ++result;
12221  }
12222  ++first;
12223  }
12224 
12225  size_t out = last - result;
12226  erase_watch(result, last);
12227 
12228  return out;
12229 }
12230 
12231 /**
12232  * \brief Insert member to statements
12233  */
12234 WatchVector::const_iterator WatchStatement::insert_watch(WatchVector::const_iterator position, const std::shared_ptr<Watch>& n) {
12235  n->set_parent(this);
12236  auto pos_it = const_iter_cast(statements, position);
12237  return statements.insert(pos_it, n);
12238 }
12239 
12240 /**
12241  * \brief Reset member to statements
12242  */
12243 void WatchStatement::reset_watch(WatchVector::const_iterator position, Watch* n) {
12244  //set parents
12245  n->set_parent(this);
12246 
12247  statements[position - statements.begin()].reset(n);
12248 }
12249 
12250 /**
12251  * \brief Reset member to statements
12252  */
12253 void WatchStatement::reset_watch(WatchVector::const_iterator position, std::shared_ptr<Watch> n) {
12254  //set parents
12255  n->set_parent(this);
12256 
12257  statements[position - statements.begin()] = n;
12258 }

12869  expression->set_parent(this);
12870  }

12873  item->set_parent(this);
12874 
12875  }
12876 
12877  }

12953  void ReactionStatement::visit_children(visitor::Visitor& v) {

12955  reaction1->accept(v);
12956  (void)v;

12962  this->reaction2->accept(v);
12963  }
12964  (void)v;
12965  /// use -> for pointer member
12966  expression1->accept(v);
12967  (void)v;
12968  /// optional member could be nullptr
12969  if (this->expression2) {
12970  this->expression2->accept(v);
12971  }
12972  (void)v;
12973  }

13014  /// copy constructor implementation
13015  ReactionStatement::ReactionStatement(const ReactionStatement& obj) {
13016  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
13017  if (obj.reaction1) {
13018  this->reaction1.reset(obj.reaction1->clone());
13019  }
13020  /// object member can be just copied by value
13021  this->op = obj.op;
13022  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
13023  if (obj.reaction2) {
13024  this->reaction2.reset(obj.reaction2->clone());
13025  }
13026  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
13027  if (obj.expression1) {
13028  this->expression1.reset(obj.expression1->clone());
13029  }
13030  /// pointer member must be reseted with the new copy
13031  if (obj.expression2) {
13032  this->expression2.reset(obj.expression2->clone());
13033  }
13034 
13035  /// if there is a token, make copy
13036  if (obj.token) {
13037  this-> token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
13038  }
13039 
13040  /// set parents
13041  set_parent_in_children();
13042  }

13571 
13572  /// if there is a token, make copy
13573  if (obj.token) {
13574  this-> token = std::shared_ptr<ModToken>(obj.token->clone());
13575  }

13579  }

14426 /**
14427  * \brief Erase member to variables
14428  */
14429 GlobalVarVector::const_iterator Global::erase_global_var(GlobalVarVector::const_iterator first) {
14430  auto first_it = const_iter_cast(variables, first);
14431  return variables.erase(first_it);
14432 }
14433 /**
14434  * \brief Erase members to variables
14435  */
14436 GlobalVarVector::const_iterator Global::erase_global_var(GlobalVarVector::const_iterator first, GlobalVarVector::const_iterator last) {
14437  auto first_it = const_iter_cast(variables, first);
14438  auto last_it = const_iter_cast(variables, last);
14439  return variables.erase(first_it, last_it);
14440 }
14441 /**
14442  * \brief Erase non-consecutive members to variables
14443  *
14444  * loosely following the cpp reference of remove_if
14445  */
14446 size_t Global::erase_global_var(std::unordered_set<GlobalVar*>& to_be_erased) {
14447  auto first = variables.begin();
14448  auto last = variables.end();
14449  auto result = first;
14450 
14451  while (first != last) {
14452  // automatically erase dangling pointers from the uset while
14453  // looking for them to erase them in the vector
14454  if (to_be_erased.erase(first->get()) == 0) {
14455  reset_global_var(result, *first);
14456  ++result;
14457  }
14458  ++first;
14459  }
14460 
14461  size_t out = last - result;
14462  erase_global_var(result, last);
14463 
14464  return out;
14465 }
14466 
14467 /**
14468  * \brief Insert member to variables
14469  */
14470 GlobalVarVector::const_iterator Global::insert_global_var(GlobalVarVector::const_iterator position, const std::shared_ptr<GlobalVar>& n) {
14471  n->set_parent(this);
14472  auto pos_it = const_iter_cast(variables, position);
14473  return variables.insert(pos_it, n);
14474 }

15295 }
15296 /**
15297  * \brief Erase non-consecutive members to blocks
15298  *
15299  * loosely following the cpp reference of remove_if
15300  */
15301 size_t Program::erase_node(std::unordered_set<Node*>& to_be_erased) {
15302  auto first = blocks.begin();
15303  auto last = blocks.end();
15304  auto result = first;
15305 
15306  while (first != last) {
15307  // automatically erase dangling pointers from the uset while
15308  // looking for them to erase them in the vector
15309  if (to_be_erased.erase(first->get()) == 0) {
15310  reset_node(result, *first);
15311  ++result;
15312  }
15313  ++first;
15314  }
15315 
15316  size_t out = last - result;
15317  erase_node(result, last);
15318 
15319  return out;
15320 }
15321 
15322 /**
15323  * \brief Insert member to blocks
15324  */
15325 NodeVector::const_iterator Program::insert_node(NodeVector::const_iterator position, const std::shared_ptr<Node>& n) {
15326  n->set_parent(this);
15327  auto pos_it = const_iter_cast(blocks, position);
15328  return blocks.insert(pos_it, n);
15329 }
15330 
15331 /**
15332  * \brief Reset member to blocks
15333  */
15334 void Program::reset_node(NodeVector::const_iterator position, Node* n) {
15335  //set parents
15336  n->set_parent(this);
15337 
15338  blocks[position - blocks.begin()].reset(n);
15339 }
15340 
15341 /**
15342  * \brief Reset member to blocks
15343  */
15344 void Program::reset_node(NodeVector::const_iterator position, std::shared_ptr<Node> n) {
15345  //set parents
15346  n->set_parent(this);
15347 
15348  blocks[position - blocks.begin()] = n;
15349 }
